---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <header class="mb-12 text-center" transition:animate="fade">
      <h1 class="text-7xl mb-8 font-bold text-black dark:bg-gradient-to-r dark:from-green-400 dark:to-cyan-400 dark:bg-clip-text dark:text-transparent">About</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-muted-foreground">
        Digital Education professional working in Higher Education
      </p>
    </header>
    
    <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none" transition:animate="fade">
  <p>
    I'm Ross Parker, a Digital Education professional with over 10 years of experience in Higher Education. 
    My work spans digital assessment, active learning, accessibility, learning analytics, and more — 
    with a particular passion for using technology to make education more effective and inclusive.
  </p>

  <h2>Notable Work</h2>

  <p>
    In 2025 I co-wrote Durham University's first Open Educational Resources (OER) policy, helping to 
    establish a formal framework for how the institution creates and shares open educational content.
  </p>

  <p>
    A significant part of my role involves making the case for new technologies — I've written several 
    business cases for the introduction of tools such as Numbas (a dedicated e-assessment platform), 
    Chirun (a tool for converting LaTeX source code into accessible web pages), and Poll Everywhere, 
    among others. Alongside this, I've developed practical workflows to support these tools, including 
    a process for converting LaTeX to Word using Pandoc and a custom macro.
  </p>

  <p>
    I have a long-standing interest in the use of video in education, having designed workshops and 
    presented at various conferences on the subject. This includes playing a key role in the rollout 
    of Durham University's lecture capture solution, Encore, and being invited to present at the 
    Panopto North American User Conference in Seattle in 2019.
  </p>

  <p>
    I've also collaborated with academic staff and students on a range of small research projects, 
    including using Augmented Reality to simulate lab experiments, creating 3D renderings of geological 
    outcrops to support more accessible field trips, and contributing to VisualPDE — a project that 
    brings interactive science and mathematics visualisations to the web.
  </p>

  <h2>Background</h2>

  <p>
    I hold a Master's in Digital Education from the University of Edinburgh and am currently studying a 
    Postgraduate course in Senior Leadership at Durham Business School.
  </p>

  <h2>This Blog</h2>

  <p>
    This is where I write about digital education, accessibility, ed-tech, and the projects I'm working on. 
    If any of that resonates with you, feel free to get in touch.
  </p>
</div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>